<task id="060" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Migrate shared `SummarizeFilesDialog.tsx` to canonical `<SendEmailStep />` wrapper</title>
    <phase>Wave 4 — SummarizeFiles Migration</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>055, 021</dependencies>
    <blocks>063</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, communication, refactoring, migration</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Removes inline `fetch` to `/api/communications/send` from a shared-lib production-shipped component (line 436 — empirically confirmed); changes a wizard step's send behavior; must respect ADR-033 (canonical send-email pattern) + ADR-019 (typed error contract) + ADR-021 (Fluent UI v9). Highest-leverage FR-15 deliverable since `@spaarke/ui-components` is consumed by multiple solutions.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Sequential: blocks 063 (deploy) which requires the migrated code shipped. Cannot parallelize with 061 (LegalWorkspace fork deletion) — fork deletion depends on the shared canonical being live first to avoid breaking the LegalWorkspace consumer.</parallel-reason>
    <fr-refs>FR-15</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Migrate `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SummarizeFilesWizard/SummarizeFilesDialog.tsx` to use the canonical `<SendEmailStep />` wrapper from the `EmailComposer` module. Remove the inline `fetch` to `/api/communications/send` at line 436 (empirically confirmed per CLAUDE.md row 6).

    Empirical state: `SummarizeFilesDialog.tsx` contains an inline send-email implementation at line 436. This is the LATENT DUPLICATION case spec FR-15 targets — even though the wizard ALSO uses a `SendEmailStep` step elsewhere, the dialog has its own bypass path. After this task, the file MUST contain zero `fetch.*communications/send` references.

    Post-migration acceptance: the SummarizeFiles wizard's email-send step is `<SendEmailStep />` (canonical wrapper); the dialog parent uses `composerRef.current.send()` to invoke send when the user clicks the wizard's Finish action. The inline `fetch` block and any colocated request-body construction are deleted.

    Note: SummarizeFilesDialog is one of the most-touched components in the shared lib (consumed by the SummarizeFilesWizard solution + previously by LegalWorkspace's fork). Treat carefully — preserve all non-send-related behavior (file selection, summary generation orchestration, etc.).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend developer authoritative on `@spaarke/ui-components` SummarizeFilesWizard surface. Familiar with the wizard step pattern (composerRef + imperative handle), the canonical `<SendEmailStep />` wrapper signature per FR-02, and the latent-fetch anti-pattern this migration replaces.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SummarizeFilesWizard/SummarizeFilesDialog.tsx` consumes `<SendEmailStep />` (or the wizard's email step uses the canonical wrapper internally). Zero `fetch.*communications/send` references in the file. `@spaarke/ui-components` builds clean. SummarizeFilesWizard surface continues to function (no regression in summary generation, file selection, wizard step navigation).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      `SummarizeFilesDialog.tsx` is the shared-lib dialog that hosts the multi-step Summarize-and-send-email wizard. The wizard's final "Send email" step previously bypassed the canonical pattern by calling `fetch('/api/communications/send', ...)` directly at line 436 — even though a wrapper called `SendEmailStep` exists in the same lib (used by other wizards like CreateMatter/Project/etc.). This is the canonical example of "latent duplication" spec FR-15 targets.

      Empirical state (CLAUDE.md row 6 + spec FR-15): inline fetch confirmed at line 436. The file ALSO has a separate `SummarizeSendEmailStep.tsx` (LegalWorkspace fork uses this name — see task 061), but the SHARED `SummarizeFilesDialog.tsx` itself contains an inline-fetch path.

      Migration approach: replace the inline `fetch` block + its surrounding handler with a mount of `<SendEmailStep />` (per FR-02 — inline mount wrapper, wizard owns the Send action via composerRef). The wizard's existing Finish-button handler invokes `composerRef.current.send()` — wrapper does the fetch internally. All side effects of the legacy fetch (state updates, dialog dismissal, parent callbacks) move into `onSent` / `onError` handlers.

      Dependencies: depends on task 055 (Wave 3 smoke pass — proves the canonical pattern works end-to-end) AND task 021 (Wave 1 `SendEmailStep` wrapper produced). Both must be landed before this task starts.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SummarizeFilesWizard/SummarizeFilesDialog.tsx (PRIMARY — migration target, line 436 inline fetch)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SummarizeFilesWizard/ (audit for related files)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailStep.tsx (canonical wrapper from Wave 1 task 021)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/communicationApi.ts (`sendCommunication()` + `SendCommunicationError`)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">MUST NOT call `fetch` to `/api/communications/send` directly. MUST use canonical wrapper.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Error path consumes typed `SendCommunicationError`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Wizard step chrome uses Fluent UI v9; canonical wrapper inherits this via NFR-03 `mount='inline'` variant.</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">No direct `@spaarke/auth` import in this file; `authenticatedFetch` flows through canonical wrapper props per shared-lib decoupling rule.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-15">Post-migration: zero `fetch.*communications/send` references in `SummarizeFilesDialog.tsx`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Preserve all non-send-related behavior of `SummarizeFilesDialog` — summary generation, file selection, wizard navigation. Only the email-send step changes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="repo">`npm run build` + `npm run lint` in `@spaarke/ui-components` MUST remain green.</constraint>
  </constraints>

