  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SummarizeFilesWizard/SummarizeFilesDialog.tsx` in full. Locate the inline `fetch` at line 436. Identify its surrounding handler function, request-body construction, success/error side effects.</step>
    <step order="2">Audit the wizard step structure: which step in the multi-step wizard hosts the email-send UX? Identify the file (likely a sibling like `SummarizeSendEmailStep.tsx` if it exists, or inline in `SummarizeFilesDialog.tsx`).</step>
    <step order="3">Read the canonical wrapper at `EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailStep.tsx` (Wave 1 task 021). Confirm prop signature: `composerRef`, `initialTo`, `initialSubject`, `initialBody`, `associations`, `attachmentSources`, `wizardContext`, `onStateChange`.</step>
    <step order="4">Sketch migration in task notes: which lines/blocks get deleted (inline fetch, inline handler, related request-body code) vs preserved (wizard navigation, file selection, summary text generation as `initialBody`).</step>
    <step order="5">Apply migration:
      - Replace the inline-fetch step UI with `<SendEmailStep />` mount
      - Pass `composerRef`, `initialBody` (the generated summary text), `attachmentSources={['wizard']}` (or appropriate sources), `wizardContext` carrying the files selected earlier in wizard
      - Wizard's Finish handler: invoke `composerRef.current.send()` instead of the legacy inline fetch
      - Replace legacy success/error side effects with `onSent` / `onError` handlers per task 051 pattern
    </step>
    <step order="6">Remove now-unused inline `fetch` code at line 436 + its handler. Remove dead imports.</step>
    <step order="7">Grep verify: `fetch.*communications/send` returns zero hits in `SummarizeFilesDialog.tsx`.</step>
    <step order="8">Run `npm run build` in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/` — verify clean.</step>
    <step order="9">Run `npm run lint` — verify clean.</step>
    <step order="10">Quality gate (Step 9.5 per FULL rigor): invoke `/code-review` on the modified file(s). Invoke `/adr-check` to verify no ADR-033 / ADR-019 / ADR-021 violations.</step>
    <step order="11">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 060 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="12">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed, advance to next pending task (061).</step>
