  <notes>
    Latent duplication context (per CLAUDE.md row 6): SummarizeFilesDialog has inline fetch at line 436 — this is the LATENT DUPLICATION case spec FR-15 calls out. Even though `<SendEmailStep />` (the canonical inline wrapper) ALSO existed (used by other wizards), this dialog bypassed it. The bypass is the bug class R3 closes.

    Distinction from LegalWorkspace fork (task 061): the shared-lib SummarizeFilesDialog.tsx (THIS task) had inline fetch. The LegalWorkspace fork at `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/SummarizeFiles/` has 9 files including `SummarizeSendEmailStep.tsx` that uses `sendCommunication()` (NOT inline fetch — but is still a fork to delete per FR-15/25). Two separate problems, two separate tasks.

    Visual / behavioral parity: the canonical `<SendEmailStep />` inline-mount variant (NFR-03) is chrome-less — it fills the wizard step container without internal header/action bar (the wizard owns navigation). If the legacy step had custom chrome (Send button rendered inline), that chrome's behavior moves to the wizard's Finish-button handler invoking `composerRef.current.send()`. Preserve the user-facing flow; just change the call path underneath.

    Smoke testing of the migrated flow happens in task 065, NOT here. This task focuses on the code change + static verification.
  </notes>

